• Graduated from university, major in Civil & Structural Engineering, and related fields;
• Having at least 3 years of working experience in structural engineering design in a foreign corporation;
• Have experience in project management over 4 years;
• Licensed as a professional engineer
• Having deep understanding of software design, structural analysis, software priority such as: ETABS, SAFE, RAPT, PLAXIS, SAP 2000, CAD, REVIT, and office software;
• Understand international construction law and design standards;
• Having the ability to read and understand technical documents, having good English communication is an advantage;
• Having sense of discipline, modern working style; having the ability to work under pressure, willing to work overtime

Benefit:
• Attractive salary with bonus
